        "In English, words like \"friend\" usually stay the same whether they\n            are the subject or the object of a sentence. In Greek, nouns are",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "inflected"
        ],
        ". This means they change their ending based on their grammatical\n            role. This process is called",
