          "The \"Flexing\" Language"
        ],
        [
          "p",
          {},
          "Think of Greek as a \"flexing\" language. Just as you flex a\n                muscle, words \"flex\" their endings to signal their function. If\n                a word is the \"doer\" (subject), it has one ending; if it's the\n                \"receiver\" (object), it has another."
        ]
      ],
